<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Flint" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Flint,</orth> 1) a stone commonly used to strike fire. <bibl n="shak. luc 176" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 176" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 176</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.90" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.317" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 317</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.111" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 111</bibl>.<lb />2) any hard stone: <cit><quote>harder than f., for stone at rain relenteth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 200" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 200</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the ruthless f. doth cut my tender feet,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 34</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I could hew up rocks and fight with f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 24</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.6.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 6, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 4, 43</bibl>. Plur. <emph>--s</emph>: <cit><quote>shards, --s and pebbles should be thrown on her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.254" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 254</bibl></cit>. Symbol of hardness: <cit><quote>love make his heart of f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.305" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 305</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 31</bibl> (Q<hi rend="sub">2</hi> F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>--s</emph>). <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 88</bibl>. <cit><quote>being incensed, he's f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 33</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.140" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 140</bibl>. <cit><quote>f. bosom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>throw my heart against the f. and hardness of my fault,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 4.9.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 9, 16</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>